items.name: Fogell / McLovin from "Superbad" (2007)
items.description:
You can support me here to be able to render better models (https://ko-fi.com/djo226). Supporters can request model.

You can also support me and get exclusive models on my Patreon.

Fogell is the tritagonist of the 2007 teen comedy film Superbad. He was played by Christopher-Mintz Plasse.

Fogell made a fake ID that reads McLovin, a 25 year old Hawaiian organ donor. He made it so that he would get Seth and Evan some booze for Jules' party. He bought some booze at a store but got punched by a thug. Two police officers arrived and met Fogell.

Prompt : Mclovin, realistic, natural lighting, post-processing, ultra realistic, highly detailed, very detailed, cinematic, hyper realistic, intricate scenery, sharp, photo by Annie Leibovitz, film, studio lighting, detailed skin, ultra realistic, bokeh, sharp features <lora:Mclovin:0.8>

Negative prompt: (deformed iris, deformed pupils, semi-realistic, cgi, 3d, render, sketch, cartoon, drawing, anime, mutated hands and fingers:1.4), (deformed, distorted, disfigured:1.3), poorly drawn, bad anatomy, wrong anatomy, extra limb, missing limb, floating limbs, disconnected limbs, mutation, mutated, ugly, disgusting, amputation

Steps: 90, Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras, CFG scale: 12, Seed: -1, Face restoration: GFPGAN, Size: 768x1024, Model hash: 81086e2b3f, Model: realisticVisionV20_v20

Face restoration is optional, may provide better result if not activated.

Use Mclovin as trigger.

New process to get better result :

Set a prompt with a low weight (like <lora:Mclovin:0.4>) and the action/situation you want (even with a lower resolution like 512x768, it'll be faster and avoid duplicate). Send the result of your choice to img2img, set the weight to <lora:Mclovin:0.8>, set a higher resolution but keep proportion. Enjoy!

items.name: RealCartoon-Pixar
items.description:
Want to buy me coffee? (Buy a cup)

Updates: 9/13/23 - Uploaded Version 3!

A branch off CheckPoint from RealCartoon3D

The Process:


This Checkpoint is a branch off from the RealCartoon3D checkpoint. This one's goal is to produce a more "Pixar" look overall. I really enjoy the 3D cartoony look and wanted to create something that would hopefully have the quality of RealCartoon3D, but in a PIXAR style. The process is the same as the base checkpoint (RealCartoon3D); but I look for more "cartoon style" merges. This (like the others) gets updates from RealCartoon3D as well (in fact this is what really drives this branch off as the PIXAR look is not as common a checkpoint to have variation from). As with the base model, I try not to use checkpoints that are restricted on merges.

The Settings:

  • Width: 512 (normally would not adjust unless I flipped the height and width)

  • Height: 768 (Have done up to 1024, but 768 was my sweet spot)

  • Sampling Method: "Eular A" became pretty much the default as versions moved along, but "DPM++ SDE Karra" and "DPM++ 2M Karras" are favorites for me as well.

  • Sampling steps: 30-50 normally (30 being my starting point, but going up to 45 a lot of the time)

  • Hires.fix settings: Upscaler (R-ESRGAN 4x+, 4k-UltraSharp most of the time), Hires Steps (10), Denoising Str (0.34 - 0.45 normally), Upscale (1.5 or 2 does well)

  • Clip Skip: 2

Would run ADetailer to help enhance the eyes but many times in the later versions I would not run this as it was not needed.

Why So Many Versions:

Because I wanted to share all the results that I felt reached a desired outcome. Allowed me to have fun, and I saw that many enjoyed them. Which motivated me to keep trying. Again, thank you.

Eva Longoria is an American actress, mainly known for her role as Gabrielle Solis in the TV show Desperate Housewives.

Note: You should also check @sstylerdurden879's great version of 2000s Eva.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there.   6. If you don't get what you want, do not review the bomb, there could be other creators' models or Lora that can get better results than mine, use theirs instead, and leave a good review on them too, support any other creators for their hard works!

NOTE: I will keep updating more actresses in versions update

===

Usage Guide

--

A. Lora Weight

  • 0.1 ~ 0.4 -- is to combine multiple faces or features, or if you experience overbaking

  • 0.5 ~ 0.7 -- is a balanced weight to get still accurate features but with more flexibility

  • 0.8 ~ 1.0 -- is to create an accurate representation of the features.

B. CFG Scale

  • A lower CFG Scale means AI gets more creative and less overbaking problems.

  • A higher CFG Scale means results get very accurate with training sets and are more prone to overbaking problems.

  • Dynamic CFG Threshold, using this method allows you to bump up quality and achieve photorealistic easily, but with lycoris, I found out recently that this method actually lowers the success rate, so only use it when you are composing with a Lora / model that works fine with this method.

C. Sampling Steps, High Res Fix & Upscaling

  • I like to use sampling steps at 50, with high res steps at 20, or 1/2 of the sampling steps.

  • I find that 2M Karras works better and faster than SDE Karras. with ERSGAN 4x+ method + ERSGAN 4x for Upscaling. This method actually gives quite good results without being too sharp or too plasticky

  • Upscaling - GPFGAN @0.25, Codeformer @0.3 & Codeformer Weight @0.15 seems to yield superior results.

Enjoy.

150 prompts of attractions in Japan, gmostly buildings.

Generated with Chat GPT.

Examples:

  1. Visit the enchanting Byodo-in Temple in Uji, with its iconic Phoenix Hall and serene Pure Land garden, offering a glimpse into the world of Buddhism

  3. Step into the historic village of Shirakawa-go in Gifu, known for its traditional thatched-roof farmhouses (gassho-zukuri) that create a unique and charming landscape

  8. Discover the beauty of the Suizen-ji Joju-en Garden in Kumamoto, designed to represent various scenic spots from Japan and China, featuring a tranquil pond, mini-mountains, and a tea house

  9. Visit the iconic Tokyo Skytree, one of the tallest towers in the world, offering breathtaking views of the cityscape and beyond from its observation decks

  10. Wander through the traditional samurai district of Kakunodate in Akita, with its well-preserved samurai residences, cherry tree-lined streets, and historic atmosphere

Thanks to its vast dataset, the model enables you to blend multiple styles together, resulting in the creation of unique and fresh styles born from the fusion of existing ones.

Other models tend to become quite similar to each other over time, losing their ability to break free from their inherent style. After some time of dedicated training on a wide-ranging dataset, Rubber Duck has achieved a flexibility similar to the original 1.5 model, while delivering a higher generation quality closer to SDXL. But that's boastful, so I'd be delighted if you give it a try and assess the model yourself! :)

modelVersions.description:
Based on origin model:

  • teacher CG increased to ~200 pcs. repeat twice.

  • regularization image contains different model generated images

    • 34 city images (from conterfeit 3)

    • 13 girl images (not limited to one model)

    • 34 nsfw images (not limited to one model)

    • 2 blank images

  • optimizer: prodigy

  • with flip augmentation

This run takes one full day to complete training. Epoch 10 is overfitting too much. Epoch 7 should be the sweet spot, but I start the run with save every 2 epochs.

Introducing Interstellar Style Model: Embracing the Aesthetics of Interstellar

Interstellar Style Model, trained for 10 epochs and 5370 steps, embodies the captivating aesthetics of the movie Interstellar. Drawing inspiration from the film's visual style, the model excels at generating images that capture the grandeur of space, the vastness of cosmic landscapes, and the awe-inspiring celestial imagery that defines Interstellar. With its training, Interstellar Style Model empowers users to effortlessly recreate the immersive visuals and cinematic atmosphere of Interstellar, enabling them to embark on their own creative journeys in the realm of space exploration.
